"NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I tried this code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\npub fn main() {\r\n    let value = 0.0f32;\r\n    unsafe { core::arch::asm!(\"mcr p0, #0, {x}, 0, 0, #0\", x = in(reg) value, options(nomem, nostack)) }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nconfig.toml file:\r\n```toml\r\n[target.thumbv8m.main-none-eabihf]\r\nrustflags = [\r\n    \"-C\", \"link-arg=--nmagic\",\r\n    \"-C\", \"link-arg=-Tlink.x\",\r\n\r\n    # Code optimizations\r\n    #\"-Z\", \"trap-unreachable=no\",\r\n    \"-C\", \"inline-threshold=5\",\r\n    \"-C\", \"no-vectorize-loops\",\r\n]\r\n\r\n[build]\r\ntarget = \"thumbv8m.main-none-eabihf\"\r\n```\r\nI expected to see this happen:\r\n\r\nCorrect compilation of the MCR instruction. This instruction is a valid ARMv8m instruction available in thumb mode. It moves a register's value and some operands into a coprocessor.\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nerror: invalid instruction\r\n  |\r\nnote: instantiated into assembly here\r\n --> <inline asm>:1:2\r\n  |\r\n1 |     mcr p0, #0, r0, 0, 0, #0\r\n  |     ^\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.65.0-nightly (02654a084 2022-08-30)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: 02654a0844f5c8d29bac318c3c6c666da3d8543d\r\ncommit-date: 2022-08-30\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.65.0-nightly\r\nLLVM version: 15.0.0\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n<details><summary>Backtrace</summary>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror: invalid instruction\r\n  |\r\nnote: instantiated into assembly here\r\n --> <inline asm>:1:2\r\n  |\r\n1 |     mcr p0, #0, r0, 0, 0, #0\r\n  |     ^\r\n```\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n</details>\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "spcan", "id": 32984627, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMyOTg0NjI3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/32984627?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/spcan", "html_url": "https://github.com/spcan", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/spcan/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/spcan/fol